  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "You are given an integer N (1 \u2264 N \u2264 10\u00b9\u2078).\n\nLet:\n\nThe rightmost digit be position 1\n\nNext digit position 2\n\nAnd so on\u2026\n\nYou must compute:\n\nSum of digits whose positions are prime numbers,\n\nthen output the sum modulo 1000000007.\n\nPositions:\n\nRightmost \u2192 1  \nNext \u2192 2  \nNext \u2192 3 \u2026  \n\n\nPrime positions are: 2,3,5,7,11,13\u2026\n\nExample\n\nInput:\n\n987654\noutput:\n19\n\n| Digit | Position | Prime? |\n| ----- | -------- | ------ |\n| 4     | 1        | No     |\n| 5     | 2        | \u2714 Yes  |\n| 6     | 3        | \u2714 Yes  |\n| 7     | 4        | No     |\n| 8     | 5        | \u2714 Yes  |\n| 9     | 6        | No     |\n\nPrime positions are: 2, 3, 5\n\nSo we pick digits at those positions:\n\nPosition 2 \u2192 digit 5\n\nPosition 3 \u2192 digit 6\n\nPosition 5 \u2192 digit 8\n\n5 + 6 + 8 = 19\n\nOutput:\n19",
    "constraints": [
      "N (1 \u2264 N \u2264 10\u00b9\u2078)"
    ],
